<item>
            <title>[MATH-1477] MillerUpdatingRegression: ArrayIndexOutOfBounds when calling regress with variablesToInclude parameter</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/MATH-1477</link>
                <project id="12310485" key="MATH">Commons Math</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;When performing a regression with a subset of predictors, an ArrayIndexOutOfBounds exception will occur for certain subset selections. For example, this appears to happen consistently for regressions without a constant term when the predictor at index 0 is not selected.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I do not understand at all the algorithm used to reorder the predictors when a subset is requested, but the fix appears to be a simple correction to the indexing range in the for-loop in the regress method of MillerUpdatingRegression.java.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&#160;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Patch with expanded unit test to follow shortly.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
